cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of inferring high-resolution hyperspectral images from low-resolution multispectral images, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves regularization techniques (cs.IR) and optimization algorithms (cs.MM) to solve the problem. Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale data processing (cs.DS) due to the very large size of the hyperspectral images.
